<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-286-370  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 286 370.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Business  May 15 1989 v15 n10 p73(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Preventive law: protecting your interests beforehand.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brumback, Nancy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Electronics executives can benefit from preventive law, whichprovides advice about risks and opportunities as decisions aremade and reviews the company and its procedures and contracts toavoid possible legal problems in the future.andP;  A preventive lawyercan make explicit the fiduciary and legal responsibilities ofexecutives and review a company's contracts and documents.andO;Preventive law is easier with an in-house counsel, but a smallerfirm can use an outside lawyer.andP;  Executives using preventive laware advised to select a lawyer who appreciates the risks at stake,to involve the lawyer early in decision making, and to have thelawyer discuss the company's strategic direction with topmanagement.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Legal IssuesManagementOrganization StructureRisk AnalysisGoals and ObjectivesDecision MakingElectronic Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>